        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-10-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-10-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="428"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d428">
                <head>428. Memorandum From the Secretary of the Joint Chiefs of Staff (<persName
                        corresp="#p_WBGRD1" type="from">Wentworth</persName>) to the Chairman of the
                    Joint Chiefs of Staff (<persName corresp="#p_RAAW1" type="to"
                        >Radford</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d428fn1">Source:
                            <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> Records, OCJCS 091 Palestine (Jun
                        56–Dec 56). Top Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-10-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 30, 1956</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> Actions with respect to the Middle East
                        Situation agreed upon at <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> Meeting 30
                        October 1956</item>
                </list>
                <p>At their meeting on 30 October 1956 the Joint Chiefs of Staff agreed to take the
                    following actions with respect to the Middle East situation: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Send a memorandum to the Secretary of Defense requesting him to ask
                            the State Department to secure the necessary authorization from the
                            Government of Turkey to station a U.S. air task group at Adana, Turkey,
                            in order to be prepared to assist in carrying out any directives which
                            may be issued by the United Nations.<note n="2" xml:id="d428fn2">In
                                response to this memorandum, Secretary of Defense <persName
                                    corresp="#p_WCE1">Wilson</persName> on October 30 sent a letter
                                to Secretary <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName>
                                requesting that the Department of State take action to acquire
                                certain base rights requirements and overflight rights in order to
                                move a substantial number of planes and accompanying Air Force
                                personnel into the Middle East to help evacuate U.S. citizens.
                                (Department of State, Central Files, 711.56300/10–3056) A
                                supplemental memorandum on this subject from <persName
                                    corresp="#p_RAAW1">Radford</persName> to <persName
                                    corresp="#p_WCE1">Wilson</persName> of November 1 was
                                subsequently transmitted to Secretary <persName corresp="#p_DJF1"
                                    >Dulles</persName> by Assistant Secretary of Defense <persName
                                    corresp="#p_GG1">Gray</persName> on November 3. (<hi
                                    rend="italic">Ibid</hi>., 711.56300/11–356)</note>
                        </item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Request representation from the Joint Chiefs of Staff of one general
                            or flag officer (from JMEPC) on the Near East Watch Committee. The
                            Chairman stated he would undertake with the State Department to secure
                            this membership.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WBGRD1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Wentworth</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
